The Valley of the Planets, also known as Kawakeb, is one of the world's natural wonders, nestled in the Wan Tikofi valley of the Libyan desert, near the mountain town of Ghat in southwest Libya. This awe-inspiring location is renowned for its unique rock formations, known as trovants, which bear an uncanny resemblance to planets in the solar system. These geological marvels have captured the human imagination for centuries due to their mysterious origins and remarkable characteristics. Unlike ordinary rocks, these trovants seem almost alive they grow, move, and even reproduce in a way that mirrors living organisms. When broken, their interiors reveal concentric circles, reminiscent of tree rings, further fueling the belief that these are not just stones, but "living" or "moving" entities.
